terrapeer.vui.j3dui.control.inputs.sensors
Class AwtKeyboardArrowSensor

java.lang.Object
  terrapeer.vui.j3dui.control.inputs.sensors.AwtKeyboardArrowSensor
Deprecated. Replaced by AwtKeyboardDragSensor for naming consistency and to conform with new pattern for AWT-based event sensors.

public class AwtKeyboardArrowSensor
extends java.lang.Object

An AWT input sensor that monitors arrow key activity, which is interpreted as a relative drag (i.e. always starts at (0,0)). Events are generated when any arrow key goes down, any arrow keys go up, and at a regular time interval while any arrow key is down. A single key press generates a delta of +/-1. Key repeats accumulate simulating a drag. Multiple arrows keys can be used at the same time.

Relying on key repeats is unreliable when multiple arrow keys are used since the repeat is often prematurely terminated. As such an internal timer is used for key repeats. Use setTimeDelays() to set the initial and key repeat times.

Only a single event source can be handled at a time. If a new source occurs during an active drag the old drag will be stopped and a new one started with the new source.
